Module 2: HTML Text & Media Elements – Mastery Notes 

2.1 Headings

HTML provides six levels of headings:

<h1>Main Title</h1>
<h2>Subheading</h2>
<h3>Section</h3>
<h4>Subsection</h4>
<h5>Smaller Subsection</h5>
<h6>Smallest</h6>

Use one <h1> per page (semantic importance).

Do not skip heading levels (e.g., <h2> should not directly jump to <h4>).

2.2 Paragraphs & Line Breaks

<p>This is a paragraph.</p>
<br />
<p>Another paragraph.</p>

<p>: Defines paragraphs.

<br>: Inserts a line break; avoid overusing.

2.3 Text Formatting Tags

Semantic Formatting

<strong>Important</strong>
<em>Emphasized</em>
<mark>Highlighted</mark>
<code>Code</code>
<abbr title="HyperText Markup Language">HTML</abbr>

Non-Semantic (Visual only)

<b>Bold (non-semantic)</b>
<i>Italic (non-semantic)</i>
<u>Underline</u>
<sup>Superscript</sup>
<sub>Subscript</sub>

2.4 Lists: Ordered, Unordered, Description

Unordered List

<ul>
  <li>Item A</li>
  <li>Item B</li>
</ul>

Ordered List

<ol>
  <li>Step 1</li>
  <li>Step 2</li>
</ol>

Description List

<dl>
  <dt>HTML</dt>
  <dd>A markup language.</dd>
</dl>

2.5 Images

<img src="logo.png" alt="Company Logo" width="200" height="100" />

src: Path to image

alt: Accessibility, SEO

width/height: Optional but improves layout rendering speed

Best Practices

Always include alt text

Use descriptive filenames

Use modern formats like WebP for optimization

2.6 Audio & Video

Audio

<audio controls>
  <source src="sound.mp3" type="audio/mpeg" />
  Your browser does not support the audio element.
</audio>

Video

<video controls width="640" height="360">
  <source src="video.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
  Your browser does not support the video tag.
</video>

Attributes

controls: Show playback controls

autoplay, loop, muted, poster

2.7 Best Practices & Accessibility

Provide alt for images, captions for media

Don’t use media (e.g., flashing video) that may cause seizures

Avoid auto-playing audio

Use <figure> and <figcaption> for annotated images

2.8 Deprecated or Avoidable Tags

Tag

Status

Reason

<font>

Deprecated

Use CSS instead

<center>

Deprecated

Use CSS: text-align

<b>, <i>

Avoid if possible

Prefer <strong>, <em>

2.9 Practice Exercise

Recreate a blog post layout:

Use <h1> to <h3> for headings

Include paragraphs and line breaks

Add a list of key points (unordered list)

Embed an image and a video
